    ###### Aim: To reverse a string in Java
    ###### Problem: The program should take a string from user and print out the same string but in reverse order.
    ###### Solution: In this case we are using StringBuilder Class which has built-in method called reverse() which can help us achieve our goal. We first create object of StringBuilder class by passing the string value to constructor. Then we call reverse() method on this object and store returned value into another variable. Finally we use println() method to display the result.
    ###### Complexity Analysis: Time complexity O(n), where n is number of characters in input string. Space complexity O(1).
    ###### Code Implementation:
    ```java
    import java.util.*;
    public class Main_4 {
      public static void main(String []args){
          //Create Objects
          Scanner scan=new Scanner(System.in);

          //Getting User Input
          String s=scan.nextLine();

          //Creating Object Of StringBuilder Class By Passing Value Of S To Constructor
          StringBuilder sb=new StringBuilder(s);

          //Calling Reverse Method On Object Created Earlier And Storing Returned Value In Another Variable
          String rev=sb.reverse().toString();

          //Printing Result
          System.out.print(rev+"\n");
      }
    }`
    ```
